Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
add_decomp_filler(25.10)                              add_decomp_filler(25.10)

Name
       add_decomp_filler  - Inserts breaker cells to divide the chip into sev-
       eral small parts

Syntax
       add_decomp_filler

       [-help]

       -bottom_edge_endcap {<cell_name>}

       -core_column_cell {<cell_name>}

       -core_row_cell {<cell_name_list>}

       [-offsetx <offset_in_microns>]

       [-offsety <offset_in_microns>]

       [-power_domain <power_domain_name>]

       [-prefix <prefix_name>]

       -stepx <step_in_microns>

       -stepy <step_in_microns>

       -top_edge_endcap {<cell_name>}

       -vertical_edge_endcap {<cell_name>}

       Inserts breaker cells to divide the chip into several small parts. This
       reduces the run time of coloring while manufacturing the chip.

       This command is run after floorPlan and before addEndCap.

Parameters
       -bottom_edge_endcap {<cell_name>}
              Specifies the CA-break end cap  cell  for  rows,  to  make  bot-
              tom_edge of endcap face core.

       -core_column_cell {<cell_name>}
              Specifies the CA-break filler cell for inserting into columns.

       -core_row_cell {<cell_name_list>}
              Specifies  a list of CA-break filler cells inserted horizontally
              in the core rows.

       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes type and  default  in-
              formation for each add_decomp_filler parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man add_decomp_filler.

       -offsetx <offset_in_microns>
              Specifies  the  offset added to the first step in the horizontal
              direction.

       -offsety <offset_in_microns>
              Specifies the offset added to the first step in the vertical di-
              rection.

       -power_domain <power_domain_name>
              Specifies the power domain for which CA-break filler  cells  are
              to be inserted.

              Note:  If  the -power_domain option is used, the offset value is
              applied to the specified power domain. However,  if  the  -power
              domain  is  not  specified,  the  offset value is applied to all
              available power domains. To use different  offset  value  for  a
              specific  power  domain, you first need to delete the CA fillers
              from the power domain if it is already filled and then  reinsert
              CA filler to the power domain with the target offset value.

       -prefix <prefix_name>
              Specifies  the prefix for decomp cells. If this option is speci-
              fied, the user-specified prefix is applied to all  inserted  de-
              comp fillers, else the default prefix name is used.

       -stepx <step_in_microns>
              Specifies the decomposition step in horizontal direction.

       -stepy <step_in_microns>
              Specifies the decomposition step in vertical direction.

       -top_edge_endcap {<cell_name>}
              Specifies  CA-break  end  cap cell for rows, to make top_edge of
              endcap face core.

       -vertical_edge_endcap {<cell_name>}
              Specifies CA-break end cap cell inserted at the left  and  right
              edges as end caps.

Example
       The code below shows the usage of the add_decomp_filler command.

       add_decomp_filler

       -core_row_cell {CA_ROW2 CA_ROW3} -core_column_cell {CA_COL2}

       -top_edge_endcap CA_TE -bottom_edge_endcap CA_BE

       -vertical_edge_endcap CA_LRE

       -stepx 500 -stepy 500

